{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.83",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 83,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 83 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:1",
      "text": "O God, do not keep silence; do not hold thy peace or be still, O God!",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:2",
      "text": "For lo, thy enemies are in tumult; those who hate thee have raised their heads.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:3",
      "text": "They lay crafty plans against thy people; they consult together against thy protected ones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:4",
      "text": "They say, “Come, let us wipe them out as a nation; let the name of Israel be remembered no more!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:5",
      "text": "Yea, they conspire with one accord; against thee they make a covenant—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:6",
      "text": "the tents of Edom and the Ishmaelites, Moab and the Hagrites,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:7",
      "text": "Gebal and Ammon and Amalek, Philistia with the inhabitants of Tyre;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:8",
      "text": "Assyria also has joined them; they are the strong arm of the children of Lot.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:9",
      "text": "Do to them as thou didst to Midian, as to Sisera and Jabin at the river Kishon,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:10",
      "text": "who were destroyed at En-dor, who became dung for the ground.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:11",
      "text": "Make their nobles like Oreb and Zeeb, all their princes like Zebah and Zalmunna,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:12",
      "text": "who said, “Let us take possession for ourselves of the pastures of God.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:13",
      "text": "O my God, make them like whirling dust, like chaff before the wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:14",
      "text": "As fire consumes the forest, as the flame sets the mountains ablaze,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:15",
      "text": "so do thou pursue them with thy tempest and terrify them with thy hurricane!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:16",
      "text": "Fill their faces with shame, that they may seek thy name, O Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:17",
      "text": "Let them be put to shame and dismayed for ever; let them perish in disgrace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.83.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:18",
      "text": "Let them know that thou alone, whose name is the Lord, art the Most High over all the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
